fields.name: Brisk Walking
fields.description: Walk at a purposeful pace where you can hold a conversation but feel your heart rate elevated. Great entry-level cardio for all fitness levels.

fields.name: Incline Treadmill Walk
fields.description: Set treadmill to 6--10% incline. Walk at moderate pace. Engages glutes and calves more than flat walking and burns significantly more calories.

fields.name: Jogging
fields.description: Maintain a comfortable running pace where speaking in short sentences is possible. Focus on landing mid-foot and keeping a steady rhythm.

fields.name: Cycling
fields.description: Steady-state cycling on a stationary bike or outdoors. Maintain a consistent cadence. Low-impact option that's easy on the joints.

fields.name: Sprint Intervals
fields.description: Sprint at maximum effort for 30 seconds, then walk for 90 seconds. Repeat 10 times. Maximises calorie burn and improves anaerobic capacity.

fields.name: Stair Climber
fields.description: Use a stair climber machine or real stairs at a challenging pace. Targets glutes, quads, and calves while delivering serious cardiovascular demand.

fields.name: World's Greatest Stretch
fields.description: Step into a deep lunge, place same-side hand on the floor, then rotate the opposite arm to the sky. Opens hips, thoracic spine, and hamstrings in one move.

fields.name: Hip 90/90 Stretch
fields.description: Sit with both legs at 90° angles in front and behind you. Sit tall through both hips equally. Slowly lean over the front shin to deepen the stretch.

fields.name: Thoracic Rotation
fields.description: Sit in a half-kneeling position. Place one hand behind your head and rotate your elbow toward the ceiling. Improves upper back rotation and posture.

fields.name: Deep Squat Hold
fields.description: Squat as deep as possible and hold, using your elbows to push your knees out. Ankles, hips, and thoracic spine all benefit. Use a wall for support if needed.

fields.name: Cossack Squat
fields.description: Stand wide. Shift your weight to one side, bending that knee deeply while the other leg stays straight. Alternate sides. Builds lateral hip mobility.
